gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 132, Thunder 126
gameRecap.excerpt: The Rockets won their 10th straight game as they defeated the Thunder, 132-126, in overtime. Jalen Green led the way for the Rockets with 37 points (7-11 3pt. FG), nine rebounds and seven assists, while Amen Thompson added a career-high tying 25 points and a season-high 15 rebounds in the victory. Josh Giddey notched a career-high tying 31 points, along with seven rebounds and four assists for the Thunder in the losing effort. The Rockets improve to 37-35 on the season, while the Thunder fall to 50-22.
